property.name: Item2
property.property:
Create an alias name to be used for the search term.
This will help distinguish individual search terms from each other within the application.This feature is best used when your search terms are more complex or very similar to others.
Example Search Term: 'iPhone 5 Verizon -4s -5s -5c -6' Example Alias: 'iPhone 5 VRZ'

property.name: Item3
property.property: Keywords separated by commas. Examples: iphone 5, 'iphone 4s', incredible (galaxy S5, galaxy S4) (galaxy S5) - (S1,S2,S3) Insert exactly as you would on eBay.com.Advanced search parameters are accepted.

property.name: Item7
property.property: Insert eBay category numeric ID. Up to 3 categories. Recommended to enter only one category

property.name: Item8
property.property: Item condition. You may skip this option to receive items with any condition.

property.name: Item9
property.property: The eBay country website to search for items.

property.name: Item10
property.property: Limits the result set to just those items located in the specified country. This is the 'Item Location'.

property.name: Item11
property.property: Available destination country for a shipping.

property.name: Item12
property.property: Insert your shipping zipcode. Items with calculated shipping will automatically be added to the sale price in the 'Total Price' field.

property.name: Item13
property.property: Seller names separated by comma. Maximum 10 sellers supported.

property.name: Item14
property.property: You may include or exclude sellers specified 'Sellers' column

property.name: Item15
property.property: Search delay. 1 min - perform a search request every 1 minute 30 min - perform a search request every 30 minutes, etc.

property.name: Item16
property.property: Build a filter to fine tune your searches.

property.name: Item17
property.property: You can create up to 10 Views. Each View can display results for several eBay searches. Example: One View shows results for Clothes, another View - for phones
